      "content": "hey, i think something is weird with my smart home setup. i noticed that whenever i get really stressed or upset, the temp on my thermostat drops like 4 degrees almost instantly. and the fridge makes this weird clicking sound right after. idk if it's just a coincidence but it feels like they're reacting to me??",
