      "content": "While current consumer smart home technology is not designed to read bio-signals like stress, it's possible there's an underlying environmental factor causing the correlation. Perhaps your stress causes a subtle change in your room's temperature or humidity that a more sensitive sensor is picking up, triggering the thermostat's programmed responses. You should also check if any devices are near your Wi-Fi router that might be emitting a specific frequency that your electronics are reacting to.",
